                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/565: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-20T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. Your 156, May 20, 11 a.m. We have been informed that the new German Consul
                    is scheduled to arrive at Monrovia by Air France plane on May 23, and that the
                    British Legation at Monrovia has been instructed to protest his landing. In view
                    of the considerations advanced in the Department’s No. 113, May 16, 9 p.m., you
                    should make representations similar to those of your British colleague in this
                    matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
